#. <section class="sutta" id="an10.84"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an10.84:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 10"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 10"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.84:0.2"
msgid "9. Theravagga"
msgstr "9. Senior Mendicants"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an10.84:0.3"
msgid "84. Byākaraṇasutta"
msgstr "84. Declaration"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an10.84:1.1"
msgid "Tatra kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There Venerable Mahāmoggallāna addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "an10.84:1.2"
msgid "“āvuso bhikkhave”ti."
msgstr "“Reverends, mendicants!”"

msgctxt "an10.84:1.3"
msgid "“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato mahāmoggallānassa paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Reverend,” they replied."

msgctxt "an10.84:1.4"
msgid "Āyasmā mahāmoggallāno etadavoca:"
msgstr "Venerable Mahāmoggallāna said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.156"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an10.84:2.1"
msgid "“Idhāvuso, bhikkhu aññaṃ byākaroti:"
msgstr "“Take a mendicant who declares enlightenment:"

msgctxt "an10.84:2.2"
msgid ""
"‘khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyāti "
"pajānāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I understand: “Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, "
"what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of "
"existence.”’"

msgctxt "an10.84:2.3"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ tathāgato vā tathāgatasāvako vā jhāyī samāpattikusalo "
"paracittakusalo paracittapariyāyakusalo samanuyuñjati samanuggāhati "
"samanubhāsati."
msgstr ""
"They’re pursued, pressed, and grilled by the Realized One, or by one of his "
"disciples who has the absorptions, and is skilled in attainments, in the "
"minds of others, and in the ways of another’s mind."

# BB translates “flustered” evidently accepting vijina and the admittedly dubious meaning of vijina. But I can’t see any justification for that. It seems to me that following the unusual term irina we have another unusual term vipina, both of which are more or less synonyms: a wilderness, forest, etc. http://sanskritdictionary.com/?iencoding=iast&q=vipina&lang=sans&action=Search The implication isn’t so much that they get emotionally upset, but that they “get stuck or lose their way”.
#. VAR: vicinaṃ → vipinaṃ (bj) | vijinaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "an10.84:2.4"
msgid ""
"So tathāgatena vā tathāgatasāvakena vā jhāyinā samāpattikusalena "
"paracittakusalena paracittapariyāyakusalena samanuyuñjiyamāno "
"samanuggāhiyamāno samanubhāsiyamāno irīṇaṃ āpajjati vicinaṃ āpajjati anayaṃ "
"āpajjati byasanaṃ āpajjati anayabyasanaṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"Grilled in this way they get stuck or lose their way. They come to ruin and "
"disaster."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an10.84:3.1"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ tathāgato vā tathāgatasāvako vā jhāyī samāpattikusalo "
"paracittakusalo paracittapariyāyakusalo evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca manasi "
"karoti:"
msgstr ""
"The Realized One or one of his disciples comprehends their mind and "
"investigates:"

msgctxt "an10.84:3.2"
msgid "‘kiṃ nu kho ayamāyasmā aññaṃ byākaroti—"
msgstr "‘Why does this venerable declare enlightenment, saying:"

# Note the triple-nested quotes!
msgctxt "an10.84:3.3"
msgid ""
"khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyāti "
"pajānāmī’ti?"
msgstr ""
"“I understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, "
"what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of "
"existence.’?”’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an10.84:4.1"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ tathāgato vā tathāgatasāvako vā jhāyī samāpattikusalo "
"paracittakusalo paracittapariyāyakusalo evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāti:"
msgstr "They understand:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an10.84:5.1"
msgid "‘Kodhano kho ayamāyasmā;"
msgstr "‘This venerable gets angry,"

msgctxt "an10.84:5.2"
msgid "kodhapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā bahulaṃ viharati."
msgstr "and often lives with a heart full of anger."

msgctxt "an10.84:5.3"
msgid ""
"Kodhapariyuṭṭhānaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. "
"(1)"
msgstr ""
"But being full of anger means decline in the teaching and training "
"proclaimed by the Realized One."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an10.84:6.1"
msgid "Upanāhī kho pana ayamāyasmā;"
msgstr "This venerable is hostile …"

msgctxt "an10.84:6.2"
msgid "upanāhapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā bahulaṃ viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an10.84:6.3"
msgid ""
"Upanāhapariyuṭṭhānaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. "
"(2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an10.84:7.1"
msgid "Makkhī kho pana ayamāyasmā;"
msgstr "prone to offensiveness …"

msgctxt "an10.84:7.2"
msgid "makkhapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā bahulaṃ viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an10.84:7.3"
msgid ""
"Makkhapariyuṭṭhānaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. "
"(3)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an10.84:8.1"
msgid "Paḷāsī kho pana ayamāyasmā;"
msgstr "contemptuous …"

msgctxt "an10.84:8.2"
msgid "paḷāsapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā bahulaṃ viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an10.84:8.3"
msgid ""
"Paḷāsapariyuṭṭhānaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. "
"(4)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an10.84:9.1"
msgid "Issukī kho pana ayamāyasmā;"
msgstr "envious …"

msgctxt "an10.84:9.2"
msgid "issāpariyuṭṭhitena cetasā bahulaṃ viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an10.84:9.3"
msgid ""
"Issāpariyuṭṭhānaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.157"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an10.84:10.1"
msgid "Maccharī kho pana ayamāyasmā;"
msgstr "stingy …"

msgctxt "an10.84:10.2"
msgid "maccherapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā bahulaṃ viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an10.84:10.3"
msgid ""
"Maccherapariyuṭṭhānaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye "
"parihānametaṃ. (6)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an10.84:11.1"
msgid "Saṭho kho pana ayamāyasmā;"
msgstr "devious …"

msgctxt "an10.84:11.2"
msgid "sāṭheyyapariyuṭṭhitena cetasā bahulaṃ viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an10.84:11.3"
msgid ""
"Sāṭheyyapariyuṭṭhānaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye "
"parihānametaṃ. (7)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an10.84:12.1"
msgid "Māyāvī kho pana ayamāyasmā;"
msgstr "deceitful …"

msgctxt "an10.84:12.2"
msgid "māyāpariyuṭṭhitena cetasā bahulaṃ viharati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an10.84:12.3"
msgid ""
"Māyāpariyuṭṭhānaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. (8)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an10.84:13.1"
msgid "Pāpiccho kho pana ayamāyasmā;"
msgstr "This venerable has bad desires,"

msgctxt "an10.84:13.2"
msgid "icchāpariyuṭṭhitena cetasā bahulaṃ viharati."
msgstr "and often lives with a heart full of desire."

msgctxt "an10.84:13.3"
msgid ""
"Icchāpariyuṭṭhānaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ. "
"(9)"
msgstr ""
"But being full of desire means decline in the teaching and training "
"proclaimed by the Realized One."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
#. VAR: Sati → muṭṭhassati (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an10.84:14.1"
msgid ""
"Sati kho pana ayamāyasmā uttari karaṇīye oramattakena visesādhigamena antarā "
"vosānaṃ āpanno."
msgstr ""
"When there is still more to be done, this venerable stopped half-way after "
"achieving some insignificant distinction."

msgctxt "an10.84:14.2"
msgid ""
"Antarā vosānagamanaṃ kho pana tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye parihānametaṃ’"
". (10)"
msgstr ""
"But stopping half-way means decline in the teaching and training proclaimed "
"by the Realized One.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "an10.84:15.1"
msgid ""
"So vatāvuso, bhikkhu ‘ime dasa dhamme appahāya imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ "
"virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"It’s not possible for a mendicant to achieve growth, improvement, or "
"maturity in this teaching and training without giving up these ten qualities."

msgctxt "an10.84:15.2"
msgid ""
"So vatāvuso, bhikkhu ‘ime dasa dhamme pahāya imasmiṃ dhammavinaye vuddhiṃ "
"virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjissatī’ti ṭhānametaṃ vijjatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"It is possible for a mendicant to achieve growth, improvement, or maturity "
"in this teaching and training after giving up these ten qualities.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an10.84:15.3"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
